==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inane
<hw>In*ane"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inanis</ets>.]</ety> <def>Without contents; empty; void of sense or
intelligence; purposeless; pointless; characterless; useless.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Vague and <xex>inane</xex> instincts.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>I. Taylor.</au>
-- <wordforms><wf>In*ane"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inane</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inane
<hw>In*ane"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is void or empty.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The undistinguishable <qex>inane</qex> of infinite space.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inangular</ent>⟦br⟧
